  "prompt": "What exactly is Gusto?",
  "response": "Gusto is a cloud-based platform designed to help small and medium-sized businesses manage various aspects of human resources (HR). Originally known as ZenPayroll, Gusto provides a range of services that streamline and automate tasks related to payroll processing, employee benefits, and compliance with tax and labor regulations.\n\nKey features of Gusto include:\n\n1. **Payroll Processing**: Gusto automates payroll calculations, tax filings, and direct deposits, making it easier for businesses to pay their employees accurately and on time.\n\n2. **Employee Benefits**: The platform offers the ability to manage health insurance, retirement plans, and other employee benefits, helping businesses attract and retain talent.\n\n3. **HR Tools**: Gusto includes tools for onboarding new employees, managing time off requests, tracking employee hours, and keeping employee records organized.\n\n4. **Compliance**: The platform helps businesses stay compliant with federal, state, and local labor laws by updating tax rates and filing the necessary forms on behalf of the employer.\n\n5. **User-Friendly Interface**: Gusto is designed to be intuitive and easy to use, making it accessible for businesses without a dedicated HR department.\n\nOverall, Gusto aims to simplify and enhance the way businesses handle HR tasks, allowing them to focus more on their core operations.",
